<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102201605948032></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102201605948032><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102201605948032>Quick Thought...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102201605948032#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 21st 5:30 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just wanted to share a few thoughts that I have been thinking about SKs (&amp; PLD for that matter also).<br><br>As most of you know, SKs can definitely tank in most situations.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are, however, materially behind WAR in terms of HP, and, at the end of the day, are still generally not as desired in groups as a WAR is (generally--especially at higher levels).  I believe that Verant, however, wants to make this game balanced, as fair as possible to all classes, and promotes grouping as much as possible, so I was thinking of the following steps to make SKs more desirable in groups (note that you must read ALL of the steps--you stop after the first, you will think I am smoking something...):<br><br>1)  Nerf the ratios of SK weapons.  That's right.  Tune them way down--like to the WAR level.  Ebon, MoSS, Shard of Night, whatever---lower the ratios something fierce so that even a WAR could wield them without substantially improving the damage output of a WAR.  This will serve two functions.  Firstly, it will LOWER the damage output of SKs &amp; 2) it would allow Verant to grant WAR the ability to wield ALL weapons (i.e. rid the game of the incredibly stupid logic that doesn't allow WAR to wield (substantially) ALL WEAPONS.  Clearly, this is secondary, but Im sure that it could be worked in somehow).  Additionally, it will also LOWER the damage output of an SK.<br><br>2)  Pump up an SKs HP per STA to more of a WAR level.  Im not saying make it equal, just close the gap substantially.  Its really silly to have a SK &amp; a PLD not be able to take a similar beating that a WAR can.  They are such similar classes that it doesnt really make sense to have that large of a gap.  It wasnt that way back in the original days of D&amp;D &amp; it shouldnt be here now...<br><br>3) To make up for the loss in damage per second, &amp; this is perhaps the hardest part, lower the level at which SKs get certain NEC spells.  For instance, rather than get Boil Blood at 53, say perhaps, SKs get it at 49 or something.  The earlier that SKs get better spells (particulariy damage spells), the higher the damage output of the SK.  Clearly, this part would really have to be sat down and some good thought put into it, but, at the end of the day, what we are trying to do is pattern the SK after the WAR &amp; (substantially) match the damage output of an SK vs a WAR.  They should be close.  <br><br>So, when all is said and done, SKs would be (in theory), no stronger (overall) than a WAR currently is now (save that I would suggest a change so that WAR could wield most weapons---no more silly restrictions).<br><br>A WAR would be all melee, no-frills, stand-in-your-face tough guy; would not require spells to buff himself, etc.  Just kick-your-arse tough guy.  <br><br>An SK would be able to take a similar beating, but would have to (generally) require the use of spells to produce the same damage output.<br><br>That would make a lot more sense to me, as well as increase the desirability of SKs in groups as well.  The change wouldnt have a dramatic impact on the game at all, as (in theory) what you have taken away, you have added elsewhere.<br><br>Im not sure if I have missed something--the answer is probably.  At the end of the day, however, I find it more and more frustrating that SKs (&amp; PLD) for that matter, can't take a similar beating as a WAR, which does NOT help promote equal grouping opportunities.<br><br>Anyone else think that something related to this is reasonable or am I just high &amp; people are happy with the way it is??<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
