	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Lunatic...<br><br>I'm not sure where to start here.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, I guess I will just jump into the fray.<br><br>First, I'm not sure that you can suggest &quot;nerfing&quot; the SK weapons without first addressing the issue of Offensive skill.  We lag behind our parent class significantly in Offensive skills.  If you want to increase the amount of damage a SK or Pally does in a fight, the easiest way is to just adjust our offensive skill cap.<br><br>Second, HP's are of no issue unless you have the AC to protect those HP's.  From what I have read, it seems that the average &quot;high end&quot; SK will have an AC of around 1,100 but the average Warrior of similar level will be around 1,400.  (We can talk about the &quot;Soft AC Cap&quot; if you wish at this point, but let's not if we don't have to.)  This means that the warrior not only will have more HP's than we do, but will be taking less damage everytime they get hit.  Add into this, the warrior's &quot;Defensive disipline&quot; and it would take a lot of tweaking for us to even come close to being able to tank (take damage) as well as warriors.<br><br>As far as spells, I agree with you.  The SK line of spells need to go higher into the Necro's line of spells to increase our damage output.<br><br>I could think of a few other things that would be nice.  Faster refresh time on HT...making the AAXP HTs on a different timers so you could use all of them in an hour instead of just one...a harm shield of some sort...an all-in-one debuff of AC,ATK,and Str....a haste buff/debuff that actually stacks with spells from other classes.  All of these things would be handy...and not unbalancing in my opinion.  However, the point is that I am not expecting anything like this to happen.  Verant is not going to look at hybrid issues until they have completed caster re-balancing and even then I personally don't exspect much change.<br><br>I take it as a personal challange to be a Knight of Fear.  We are what we are.  It is up to the person behind the Shadowknight to be a great player and be able to adapt to whatever situation presents itself.<br><br>Good hunting all...see you in the land of Norrath.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
