	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok you lost me again, I thought we WERE talking about Boss MOBs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because I thought we've already agreed that SK's make great tanks for XP groups.  Yeh we could do better in the HP department, but it's only against the Big Guys that we are inadaquate to the point of not being allowed to play.<br><br>I do rely on lifetaps to balance the HP difference between me and Warriors alot.  In XP groups, with Cleric's I know I typically stay in the top 2 bubbles of health with me using lifetaps and the Cleric using Clestial Cleansing.  I also do a great deal of XP with just me and a Druid, Chloro, Superior Heal and Lifetaps keeps me alive quite well.  And if we add a warrior to that mix they stil want me to Tank for agro reasons and the Lifetap that keeps me from being so dependant on the Druids lesser heals.  <br><br>Yes I'd like more HP's, I am currently buying the extra Stamina and will soon buy the Natural Durability, Regen and every other AA Ability that adds to or regens HPs (after I get Critical Hits that is).  But, when I'm in an XP group, my HP's are within about 1k of the comperable buffed Warriors my level, and for Raids I'm above 3k with Hps and the warriors break 5k.  But my value to those that know my play style makes me far more valuable than the HP's I bring.<br><br>Discipline, yes I mean Furrious, but Auto-Rippost lets everyone understand what it does.  The Defensive is lvl 55, 15 minute reset, but for Raids they typically switch MA between pulls so that the one with Defensive up gets to be MA, we do this alot in ToV.  Defensive is just that powerful!  Furrious is a tremendous but limited discipline.  The benefit is to allow huge agro to the Main Tank without taking any damage, which defensive doesn't do (it reduces agro alot).  So basically whenever you get together 2-4 groups of people to do any Raiding, why would you take the chance of NOT having a Tank with Defensive be the Main Assist, it's on par with why would you put a Shaman healing the MA as primary healer.  When the chips go down, everyone does what they have to do, SK's jump in and Tank, Shaman heal, Rangers tank too when they are the last Melee standing and the Clerics haven't camped out yet.<br><br>I'd like to get some plus-up in Tanking, sure, but I don't want to give up Melee ability to do it.  Even if we get buffed up in defense we still will spend most Raids hitting the MOB from behind, so reducing Melee will only make us less useful 90% of the time.<br><br>Neptunis<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
