	   <tr><td colspan=2>Interesting...<br><br>At 32, with DB rod, you are definitely in great shape.&nbsp;&nbsp;DB Rod has a dmg per sec of 15.25 (not counting dmg bonus, however, also not counting dmg cap either) and the is GREAT output (wgt of 10 stinks, but...).<br><br>Anyways, based on your comment, I presume that you are trained in 1HB.  With that in mind, just to comparo shop, see how much an Ebon Mace goes for.  If you could sell DB Rod, as you are not well trained in 2HB anyways, and get an Ebon (1HB), you'd be set all the way til mid-50s EASY.  Ebon has a dmg per sec on 16.3 and you still can hold a shield.  This is presuming, of course, that you want to improve your weapon at the moment, and are not concerned about armor....<br><br>I am a big fan of 1HB for SKs.  Many top end 1HB are SK only, which helps keep the price down, and I love the envy that I get from WAR that can't wield 1/2 the weapon that SKs can (granted, they can wield TWO though...heh).  Further, several of the BEST 1HB in the GAME (in ToV) are SK and / or SK/PLD only and they are SCARY.  In other words, do NOT ignore 1HB--it helps in mid-game and definitely can at the end game.<br><br><br>I just recently acquired a 1HP (Shard of Night, from earlier post) and have been pleasantly surprised at how fast I was able to get my skill in piercing above 200.  I have a good friend that is a chanter, so I am frequently buffed with INT &amp; SPD buffs, which make weapon training go a lot faster.  However, regardless of whether you have a chanter friend or not, you will most likely be grouping with a SHM or a ENC in your 50s anyways, so all Im saying is that it isnt your death if you dont train in all your weapon skills early on.<br><br>However, if you want to train 2HB, then you are FINE for quite some time.  15.25 dmg per sec will leave many drooling over the dmg that you do &amp; you will be fine through your 40s easy.  Further, there are a few 2HB SK weapons that are frightening, but I have seen only ONE so far (Facesmasher if memory serves--they are RARE)<br><br>Anyways, hope this helps<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
