<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102140102510936></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102140102510936><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102140102510936>Breaking A Camp - New Technique of Mine</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102140102510936#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>59 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 14th 2:39 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.76]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>well i don't know if this technique is anything new - prolly not as whatever you try in this game, someone else has certainly tried it too, but here's something new i found that was a fun way to get a single pull.<br><br>i was hunting in the echo caverns with a warrior. we went up to bogling camp. problem was if we pulled we'd get like 4 of them which was tough as they were all blue to us and hit decently hard. so without crowd control even if we could win the recovery time would be ridiculous. so here's what i did.<br><br>first i killed my pet, because it would screw things up. then i had my partner drop well back near the tentacle plants (not too close). i cast shieldskin on myself so i could ignore the first few hits (key to this strategy).<br><br>i then pulled the mob of four by fearing one of them. when it worked the one ran past me and my partner towards the guards. the other three mobbed me. i immediately feigned death. this usaully went off wihout a hitch since they don't cast and shieldskin took care of the first few hits.<br><br>boglings are quick to loose aggro and return to their camp. once they did i popped up and dropped back to where my partner was.<br><br>about this time fear wore off and i prepared to hit the returning bogling with engulfing darkness. from there it was a solo battle and as you can imagine - cake.<br><br>on the off chance the bogling resisted (they don't resist much) i'd just feign, clear aggro, med a little and try again.<br><br>cool technique that cuts down on recovery time. using it we were able to completely clear the bogling room and all the shrooms at the back.<br><br>anyway, thought i'd post it. obviously to do this you HAVE to know the pathing and know that there isn't a danger of the fear runner bringing back a train. this wouldn't work everywhere certainly, but you might try it here or otherplaces.<br><br>i haven't tried it solo yet, but see no reason why it wouldn't work just as well.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
