	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well said, and I still respectfully disagree with you.<br><br>First I am somewhat spoiled in that I rarely ever fight in an XP group without C2 or KEI (the benefits of being friends with a lvl 60 Chanter for the past2 years).&nbsp;&nbsp;So yes for me, mana use is not a big deal.  And the stopping to cast on a pull is only really useful when you are pulling with a Darkness line spell, which you don't do in high tempo groups anyway.  But in the 30's and into the low 40's I pulled this way alot and was always welcome in groups as I kept the xp rolling without adds.  But yes, it's not an everyday technique but something the low levels could use.<br><br>Next, I still have never seen Torrent of Hate over-write a Shaman buff.  Will you please tell me what buffs this over-writes.  I understand the issue when you have a full buff window, but besides then I've never seen a conflict, and I Raid with full lvl 60 Shaman buffs and Chanter buffs, usually Druid buffs instead of Cleric buffs though.  So this one I really am looking for info, help me out.<br><br>Shroud of Pain is a spell I was using post-patch in Tenumbrous Mnts at the Castle.  I was with 2 groups, we had a lvl 58 Necro pulling as she new the Castle and I don't.  When she pulled, I stood just in front of the MOB and caste Torrent of Hate and never once did the MOB pass me to chase the puller or did I have a problem keeping agro with a Ranger, Rogue and Wizard in the mix.  I did switch to 1hb and a shield, but I always do that when Main Tanking anyway, but Bash does help agro alot.<br><br>Shadow Vortex is a great taunter, and yes it takes longer to caste and more mana, but it's very effective.  I was using it to pull agro before in other groups, and it will pull MOBs to you very quick unless someone has done something absolutely stupid (Ice Commet on pull for instance).  Remember I group with a Chanter almost always, I know I can get a MOB off him if MEZ fails or breaks before he's memblured it.  Shadow Vortex is awesome at this.  AND if you SV the mezzed MOBs after memblur the Chanter can sit right next to the MOB and once mez breaks the MOB ignores them and finds you.<br><br>As for out taunting Pali's, it's not tough at the high end.  They use stun alot, but for MOBs that are immune to stun this is a limited taunt.  I use alot of spells when I fight, so for a Pali to ever get anything off me when I don't want them to is very unusual.  If I do loose agro, I can always get it back quick with SV, bash and stand INSIDE the MOB when you taunt.  Getting as close to the MOB as possible is the most effective taunter in the game.  Even if the Pali s effectively stunning, just step inside of him, bash, taunt and caste SV, when stun wears off, it will hate you more anyway.  And if all else fails HT it in the mix for another taunt (every 70 minutes).<br><br>Basically we're ok with taunt still.  Some people will have to change their tactics a bit, we will have to relook at our spell line-up, but we've still got it.  And if you're not pulling sit between MOBs so you can keep the mana coming in.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
